snippet: Andy Murray became the first player to hold aloft the super-sized Queen's Club trophy for a fifth time after he beat big-serving Canadian Milos Raonic 6-7(5) 6-4 6-3 in the final of the Aegon Championships on Sunday....
lead_paragraph: Andy Murray became the first player to hold aloft the super-sized Queen's Club trophy for a fifth time after he beat big-serving Canadian Milos Raonic 6-7(5) 6-4 6-3 in the final of the Aegon Championships on Sunday.

headline.print_headline: Murray Downs Raonic to Win Record Fifth Queen's Title
headline.main: Murray Downs Raonic to Win Record Fifth Queen's Title
